Galactic ResourcesLtd said it signed a five-year revision agreement to reschedulethe net smelter royalty payments of the Summitville projectmining lease, reducing production costs by 17 U.S. dlrs anounce at gold prices of 425 U.S. dlrs an ounce.    For gold prices less than 475 dlrs an ounce the revisedroyalty schedule falls to one pct from five pct, and rises toseven pct from five pct for prices above 750 dlrs an ounce.    The royalty cost cut combined with Galactic's previouslyannounced conservative accounting change will lower chargesagainst earnings by about 69 dlrs per ounce of gold produced. Reuter&#3;